**The Winter Hexagon** — six brilliant stars forming a grand asterism spanning the winter sky:

| Star | Constellation | Color |
|------|--------------|-------|
| Sirius | Canis Major | Blue-white |
| Procyon | Canis Minor | Yellow-white |
| Pollux | Gemini | Orange |
| Capella | Auriga | Yellow |
| Aldebaran | Taurus | Orange-red |
| Rigel | Orion | Blue-white |

Orion's Betelgeuse sits at the center of the hexagon — a crimson heart for winter's crown.

